OL,3,CPolls open in Hungary in an election
OL,4,Cthat could unseat populist Orban.
OL,6,FHungarians are casting ballots on
OL,7,FSunday in what is widely seen as
OL,8,FEurope's most consequential election
OL,9,Fthis year, a vote that could unseat
OL,10,Fpopulist Prime Minister Viktor Orban,
OL,11,Fan ally of US President Donald Trump,
OL,12,Fafter 16 years in power.
OL,14,FIt is a key moment for Orban, the
OL,15,FEuropean Union's longest-serving
OL,16,Fleader and one of its biggest
OL,17,Fantagonists.
OL,19,FPolls opened at 6 am local time and
OL,20,Fare scheduled to close at 7 pm.
OL,26,@lD@_rprD@crpvD@[rp
