OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776024347
OL,3,CPolls open in Hungary in an election
OL,4,Cthat could unseat populist Orban.
OL,6,FOrban and his top challenger, Peter
OL,7,FMagyar, arrived at separate polling
OL,8,Fstations in Budapest at nearly the
OL,9,Fsame time to cast their votes.
OL,11,FSpeaking to reporters outside, Orban,
OL,12,F62, said the campaign had been "a
OL,13,Fgreat national moment on our side" and
OL,14,Fthanked activists and supporters for
OL,15,Ftheir work.
OL,17,F"I'm here to win," he said.
