OL,3,CPolls open in Hungary in an election
OL,4,Cthat could unseat populist Orban.
OL,6,FThe election was being closely watched
OL,7,Fin countries around Europe and beyond,
OL,8,Fwhich is a testament to the outsize
OL,9,Frole Orban occupies in far-right
OL,10,Fpopulist politics worldwide.
OL,12,FMembers of Trump's "Make America Great
OL,13,FAgain" movement are among those who
OL,14,Fsee Orban's government and his Fidesz
OL,15,Fpolitical party as shining examples of
OL,16,Fconservative, anti-globalist politics
OL,17,Fin action, while he is reviled by
OL,18,Fadvocates of liberal democracy and the
OL,19,Frule of law.
OL,26,@lD@_rpqD@IrptD@TOUuD@FO]vD@Hrp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
