PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776024347
OL,3,CPolls open in Hungary in an election
OL,4,Cthat could unseat populist Orban.
OL,6,FHe has also heavily strained Hungary's
OL,7,Frelationship with the EU, seeming to
OL,8,Frevel in using his veto power to
OL,9,Fstymie the 27-member bloc's important
OL,10,Fdecisions. Most recently, he blocked a
OL,11,F90-billion euro (#78 billion) EU loan
OL,12,Fto Ukraine, prompting his partners to
OL,13,Faccuse him of hijacking the critical
OL,14,Faid.
OL,16,FYet after winning four consecutive
OL,17,Felections with a two-thirds majority
OL,18,Ffor his party in Parliament, signs
OL,19,Fhave emerged that Orban's absolute
OL,20,Fcontrol over Hungary's politics may be
OL,21,Freaching its end.
OL,26,@lD@_rp{D@Vrp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
