PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776024347
OL,3,CPolls open in Hungary in an election
OL,4,Cthat could unseat populist Orban.
OL,6,FA former insider within Orban's
OL,7,FFidesz, Magyar broke with the party in
OL,8,F2024 and quickly formed Tisza. Since
OL,9,Fthen, he has toured Hungary
OL,10,Frelentlessly, holding rallies in
OL,11,Fsettlements big and small in a
OL,12,Fcampaign blitz that recently had him
OL,13,Fvisiting up to six towns daily.
OL,15,FIn an interview with The Associated
OL,16,FPress earlier this month, Magyar said
OL,17,Fthe election will be a "referendum" on
OL,18,Fwhether Hungary continues on its drift
OL,19,Ftoward Russia under Orban, or can
OL,20,Fretake its place among the democratic
OL,21,Fsocieties of Europe.
OL,26,@lD@_rpnD@\rpyD@XOUyD@cO]{D@Xrp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
