OL,3,CPolls open in Hungary in an election
OL,4,Cthat could unseat populist Orban.
OL,6,FMagyar and Tisza face a tough fight.
OL,7,FOrban's control of Hungary's public
OL,8,Fmedia, which he has transformed into a
OL,9,Fmouthpiece for his party, and vast
OL,10,Fswaths of the private media market
OL,11,Fgive him an advantage in spreading his
OL,12,Fmessage.
OL,14,FThe unilateral transformation of
OL,15,FHungary's electoral system and
OL,16,Fgerrymandering of its 106 voting
OL,17,Fdistricts by Fidesz will also require
OL,18,FTisza to gain an estimated 5% more
OL,19,Fvotes than Orban's party to achieve a
OL,20,Fsimple majority.
OL,26,@lD@_rpoD@Drp{D@Orp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
